multi session auth:

- platform should support multiple sessions at a time
- like this on client:  
  - http only cookie: session_<user>=<token>

- active session will also be stored in cookie in this format:
  - http only cookie: active_session=<token>/<user>
  - this will be used to select the active session for the current request

- in server sessions will be as ususal stored in sessions/ dir and name will be 
  session_<session_id> (which is currently working)

- /whoami will return details based on active session

- setuid() and setgid() will be used to drop privileges to the user based on current session

- new apis to be added:
  - GET /sessions
    - will return a list of all active sessions and its basic details:
    - resoponse format {session_id, username, expiry_time, last_acces_time}[]
  - DELETE /sessions/<session_id>
    - will delete the session and all its data
  - DELETE /logout
    - will delete the active session cookie
  - POST /sessions/switch/<session_id>
    - will switch the active session cookie to the new session

